So I did over a hundred informational interviews over six months, which again is extreme. I was

00:33:00.479 --> 00:33:05.199
like writing my dissertation and had more flexibility. But the reason I like to tell

00:33:05.199 --> 00:33:10.959
this story is that by the time that I applied to jobs, I only applied to maybe eight jobs. It was

00:33:10.959 --> 00:33:17.119
an extremely targeted search because I kind of knew which cultures and teams would align with what I

00:33:17.119 --> 00:33:23.920
was looking for. And I had some contact at almost every place that I applied for. And I think really

00:33:23.920 --> 00:33:29.119
notably the two places where I didn't have any contact, I never heard back from, I did not make

00:33:29.119 --> 00:33:33.920
it past the resume screen, but all of the places where I knew a little bit more or had somebody

00:33:33.920 --> 00:33:39.199
who was like a third connection, I ended up interviewing and was able to get an offer.

00:33:39.760 --> 00:33:46.560
So I think like that's kind of one story is really around the power of, when I tell this story,

00:33:46.560 --> 00:33:51.359
I often tell people, you'll either have to do a lot of work by applying to a lot of jobs, right?

00:33:51.359 --> 00:33:56.000
And do kind of a scattershot approach and just see who bites. Or you could do a lot of work up front

00:33:56.000 --> 00:34:00.400
and talk to a lot of people and then do a more selective search. So the work is there either way.

00:34:01.280 --> 00:34:05.599
And then the second thing I would say is I think it really depends on stage of company, right?

00:34:05.599 --> 00:34:09.439
So my general impression, though, Joe, you have way more experience than me,

00:34:09.439 --> 00:34:13.679
is I think some of these things are harder in larger organizations because they're just more

00:34:13.679 --> 00:34:18.560
systems, right? They're getting a lot of people. It's a larger system. There are more screens,

00:34:18.560 --> 00:34:23.600
there are recruiters. If you go smaller, and this is kind of the advice that I was given for

00:34:24.560 --> 00:34:30.239
for product at the time, I was told that basically it would be impossible for me to

00:34:30.239 --> 00:34:35.199
get a product management job with no previous experience. And I think that that is basically

00:34:35.199 --> 00:34:41.760
true. To try to break into product at a large company would have basically been almost impossible,

00:34:41.760 --> 00:34:45.760
I think, at the time. But it turns out that when I go to a smaller company,

00:34:45.760 --> 00:34:49.840
they're looking for very different things. They're looking for people who are self-starters. They're

00:34:49.840 --> 00:34:54.000
also they don't have as much leverage for hiring because they can't pay as much as like the big

00:34:54.000 --> 00:34:59.520
