Bella had this heuristic or something, which is like in any job, you can really only optimize

00:38:04.239 --> 00:38:08.239
for two things, or at least that's like a way of thinking about it. Like you can only optimize for

00:38:08.239 --> 00:38:15.199
two things and everything else that you get is like bonus or is great that it comes with a package.

00:38:15.199 --> 00:38:20.320
But once you try to optimize for more than two things, the equation gets like very complicated

00:38:20.320 --> 00:38:26.800
and the set of jobs that you can take might become too narrow. So an example is if you

00:38:26.800 --> 00:38:35.040
care about geography, pay, mission, culture, growth, you can list all these values that you

00:38:35.040 --> 00:38:41.280
have and that you want out of your next job. It probably is like doable to get something where

