we're all just people trying to figure out what work environment works best for us, and what kind

00:43:48.639 --> 00:43:53.280
of people we want to work with, and what kind of problems. And, you know, this is something I think

00:43:53.280 --> 00:43:58.000
people are not talking about when you're younger in school, which is you might like the subject,

00:43:58.000 --> 00:44:02.000
but do you like the day-to-day? Is there a particular management style that you like?

00:44:02.000 --> 00:44:07.760
You know, what's the mix of meetings and focus time that works best for you? And I think thinking

00:44:07.760 --> 00:44:13.679
about your career as a self-exploration to understand what works best for you is ultimately

00:44:13.679 --> 00:44:19.439
kind of what this is all about. So one job is just one job, but it's all building a body of knowledge

