networking. And I think that, you know, promotion is often has a has a social component. Not to say

00:51:13.760 --> 00:51:20.239
it's popularity contest, it is say like, you need to be well aligned with, you know, your lead your

00:51:20.239 --> 00:51:27.600
managers and leaders about like, what skills, what demonstrations are going to warrant that

00:51:27.600 --> 00:51:33.760
promotion. And so, you know, if you're, if you're seeking promotion within your company, like my

00:51:33.760 --> 00:51:39.760
advice would be like, start that as an explicit conversation, you know, with your manager about

00:51:39.760 --> 00:51:44.719
like, what are the skills that you know, you need to see demonstrated? What are the, you know,

00:51:44.719 --> 00:51:48.879
accomplishments that, you know, you need to see so that it's not like a mystery that arrives at the

00:51:48.879 --> 00:51:54.479
end of the year, but it's like an explicit conversation. And then, you know, you don't

00:51:54.479 --> 00:51:58.879
have to, you don't have to stop there, like, you know, look around at who else is getting promoted,

